The paper discusses a Head-Mounted Display (HMD) based augmented reality (AR) guidance system for optimal surgical arm setup, which is a topic related to robotics and healthcare. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of reflective-AR displays, which involves computer vision techniques and image processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the visualization of different perspectives simultaneously, which is related to graphics and visualization, making cs.GR (Graphics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents measurements from configuring a robotic manipulator, which involves data analysis and machine learning, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
